div.div: Bots that use UptimeRobot keeps getting rate limited

When multiple users host their Bots in the same site (for example replit) they all share similar IPs (I will not explain this in detail) What is happening is that the Discord API is ratelimiting the IP where your Bot is running. However, the webserver does not crash on Bot's errors (such as 429) so the site will be still online for uptime robot. I would suggest to look for other free hosts but where you need a credit card to use the service (e.g. oracle cloud)
